questions.explanation:
Namespaces prevent **name collisions**.

The problem: two libraries both define a function called `init()`. Without namespaces, the compiler does not know which one you mean.

The solution: put them in different namespaces. Use `::` to pick the one you want.

```cpp
namespace Graphics { void init() { /* GPU */ } }
namespace Audio    { void init() { /* sound */ } }
// Graphics::init() and Audio::init() — no conflict
```

